data.data: Here at ACM@CMU, we're proud of everything we do, and that is only possible with our amazing board members. Get to know our team.

Hi! I'm Michelle, a junior studying CS who is a 15150.5 TA (15150 + 15151). I enjoy a wide variety of activities in my free time, like sleeping, eating and sitting. In the future I'd like to remove all snakes (the animal), but with technology, and not my hands.

Hello! I'm Jocelyn, a junior studying Computer Science and concentrating in Machine Learning! At a given point in time, you can find me in Gates, pushing for CIA Buggy, sleeping, running outdoors, or eating ramen or pasta.
Hello! My name is Jonathan Chiu, and I'm currently a junior in SCS. If I'm not collapsed in some comfy chair in Gates, you can probably find me at El Gallo De Oro, the best place to eat on campus.
Hello! I'm Howard, a junior studying math and CS. I am an enjoyer of speech of the peculiar variety and lurking in Gates whilst acquiring pain from sets of the P variety.
Hey there! I'm Erica, a sophomore in CS. Catch me watching the sunset from the Gates balcony or not watching the sunset.

Hellooo, I'm Stephanie! I'm a junior majoring in CS and considering a concentration in HCI. I enjoy video games, books, and digital art, which is probably why I was drafted I mean, applied for this position.
I'm studying CS and HCI. I'd like to call myself an amateur film critique but in reality I just like watching movies and talking about them.

Hi, I'm Jackson. I'm from NYC and am currently a junior studying CS. When I'm not watching youtube or procrastinating, I like to go outside and be active. One day, I hope to dunk on my friend Michael Chen.
Hi! I'm David, a junior studying CS and Math and research assistant in the Auton Lab. Outside of school, I enjoy golfing, working out, and watching Top Gun: Maverick.
